```

### CAN interface

Linux provides CAN driver for physical available CAN controller and for virtual created CAN adapter so called vcan.

```shell
$ antonio (linux) >sudo modprobe vcan
$ antonio (linux) >lsmod | grep vcan
vcan                   12288  0
can_dev                53248  1 vcan
```

Configure an interface vcan0 type vcan with mtu 16

```shell
root@xps-ubuntu:~# ip link add dev vcan0 type vcan
root@xps-ubuntu:~# ip link set vcan0 mtu 16
root@xps-ubuntu:~# ip link set up vcan0
root@xps-ubuntu:~# ip link sh
...
7: vcan0: <NOARP,UP,LOWER_UP> mtu 16 qdisc noqueue state UNKNOWN mode DEFAULT group default qlen 1000
    link/can 
root@xps-ubuntu:~# 
```

